Conclusion:
My approach combines the strengths of automation and analytical judgment. AI and scraping tools would handle large-scale data collection and preliminary qualification, while manual validation would ensure that only genuinely differentiated, growth-oriented, and systems-driven companies are included. This process would allow DeepThought to build a reliable database of 1,000 Federer-profile companies within one month without sacrificing research quality.
